From: filamind <abdelmonemawad@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] iot_drivers/main: use Transport.create() instead of WebsocketClient

Switches the box from a hard-wired WebSocket client to the new
filamind multi-transport selector at tools/transport.py (added by
build-image.sh as a wholesale file copy).

The selector probes WS first; if the proxy in front of Odoo is broken
(e.g. OpenLiteSpeed adding `Connection: Keep-Alive` to the 101 Switching
Protocols response), it auto-falls-back to HTTP long-poll, then to
short-poll. The choice is cached in odoo.conf so subsequent boots skip
the probe.

The transport's surface (start/stop + on_message dispatch) is identical
to WebsocketClient, so iot_handlers and communication.handle_message
need no other change.

---
 addons/iot_drivers/main.py | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/addons/iot_drivers/main.py b/addons/iot_drivers/main.py
--- a/addons/iot_drivers/main.py
+++ b/addons/iot_drivers/main.py
@@ -10,6 +10,6 @@ import time

 from odoo.addons.iot_drivers.tools import certificate, helpers, system, upgrade, wifi
-from odoo.addons.iot_drivers.websocket_client import WebsocketClient
+from odoo.addons.iot_drivers.tools.transport import Transport

 if system.IS_RPI:
     from dbus.mainloop.glib import DBusGMainLoop
@@ -158,6 +158,6 @@ class Manager(Thread):
         schedule.every().monday.at("00:00").do(upgrade.check_git_branch)

         # Set up the websocket connection
-        ws_client = WebsocketClient(self.ws_channel)
+        ws_client = Transport.create(self.ws_channel)
         if ws_client:
             ws_client.start()
